State Bank of India Plans to Open Unit in Ghana, B&FT Reports

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-07-06T10:47:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/state-bank-of-india-plans-to-open-unit-in-ghana-b-ft-reports.html
State Bank of India  plans to open a
unit in  Ghana , the Business and Financial Times newspaper
reported, citing Naresh Kumar Malhotra, deputy general manager
of the bank.  The lender wants to increase the contribution of overseas
operations to group profit to 25 percent in five years from 16
percent, the Accra-based newspaper reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 